ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: improving communication skills for MS students
Mandatory workshop to practice job skills that was more stressful than it should have been
It is enjoyable and helpful! take it definitely
It is a very helpful session with a lot of practical and constructive skills for looking for those who will be looking for jobs in the industries after graduation
I will recommend it because it is helpful.
Yes everyone needs it, but I think instead of having two lessons more lessons are needs with less time for each one.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I suppose it helps to practice presenting information in your field, but we were allowed to present anything we wanted. Facilitators were unfamiliar with a lot of terms in our discipline, so the feedback about that was not super relevant to public health itself. I doubt this course will really help me with research or my thesis, as I feel I could get help with presentations from career services that is just as good.
It contributes to my professional experiences.
I realized some of the problems I have for my public speech.
